Here’s your proposal polished into a clean student-report format, ready to be used as documentation or submission:

Proposal – Flappy Bird Java
1. Introduction
This project aims to develop a simple Flappy Bird game using Java in order to practice object-oriented programming principles and game loop concepts. The game provides a straightforward yet engaging experience where the player controls a bird navigating through moving pipes while avoiding collisions.

2. Technologies Used
Programming Language: Java

IDE: NetBeans

Libraries: Java Swing / AWT

Version Control: GitHub

3. Main Features
Press the SPACE key to make the bird fly upward.

Gravity continuously pulls the bird downward.

Pipes move from right to left across the screen.

Collision detection between the bird and pipes.

Score increases when the bird passes through pipes.

The game ends when a collision occurs.

This version is concise, structured, and matches the style of a student project proposal.

